<Base title="Why 40 FPS feels so good on handhelds — Handheld Settings Lab" description="A plain-English frame pacing guide for Steam Deck and handheld PC players."><article class="wrap article"><span class="eyebrow">Guide</span><h1>Why 40 FPS feels so good on handhelds</h1><p class="muted">40 FPS is a sweet spot because it can feel much smoother than 30 FPS while using less power than an unlocked 60 FPS target.</p><h2>Quick answer</h2><p>On many handhelds, a stable 40 FPS cap paired with an 80Hz or compatible refresh-rate target gives better frame pacing for travel gaming.</p><h2>Use it when</h2><ul><li>The game cannot hold 60 FPS without noise, heat, or ugly settings.</li><li>You want better input feel than a 30 FPS cap.</li><li>You are playing on battery and want a balanced preset.</li></ul><div class="callout">Lab note: always prioritize stable frame pacing over peak FPS screenshots.</div></article></Base>
